-- Enbridge says Line 6A will restart Friday morning
-- 
-- Thu Sep 16, 2010 2:52pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/09/16/us-enbridge-leak-idUSTRE68F2J420100916

 

 HOUSTON  (Reuters) - Enbridge Inc will restart its key Line 6A crude oil pipeline on Friday morning, a company executive said on Thursday. 

 "We are preparing to safely return the pipeline to service tomorrow morning," said Enbridge Senior Vice President Art Meyer, speaking on a conference call. "We have confirmed to (U.S. Transportation Department) officials that we've completed the necessary steps for safe startup and they have acknowledged that the restart will proceed Friday morning." (Reporting by  Bruce Nichols )